{"cursor":"2774","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"A 'pitch' is an outdoor playing area for various sports. The term is used in\nBritish and Australian English; the comparable term in American English is\n'playing field'. In most sports, the official technical term is 'field of\nplay', although this is not regularly used by those outside of\nrefereeing/umpiring circles.\n\nIn the sport of cricket, the cricket pitch refers not to the entire field of\nplay, but to the section of the field on which batting and bowling take place in\nthe centre of the field. The pitch is prepared differently to the rest of the\nfield, to provide a harder surface for bowling.\n\nA pitch is often a regulation space, as in an association football pitch.\n","linknr":148,"url":"Field_of_play","recorded":1371237692,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Pitch_(sports_field)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Pitch_(sports_field)&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Pitch_(sports_field)","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Field_of_play&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/British_English","/wiki/Australian_English","/wiki/American_English","/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed","/wiki/Cricket","/wiki/Cricket_pitch","/wiki/Cricket#The_playing_field","/wiki/Regulation